OL,7,FPrince Albert is usually credited with
OL,8,Fhaving introduced the Christmas tree
OL,9,Finto England in 1840 after he and
OL,10,FQueen Victoria were famously
OL,11,Fillustrated standing beside a
OL,12,Fdecorated tree with their children.
OL,14,FTo celebrate this chapter in history,
OL,15,FJersey Heritage invited 500
OL,16,Fschoolchildren to their Victorian
OL,17,FHouse to learn all about how the
OL,18,FVictorians would have celebrated
OL,19,FChristmas.
